   <abstract>This is a letter dated August 12, 1805 from John Sevier of Tennessee to Colonel Jonathan Meigs at the Department of War. Sevier's brief letter to Meigs informs of an enclosed letter by Colonel Scott describing a massacre involving Cherokee Indians.</abstract>
